							<decoNote type="miniature">14 full-page miniatures in colours and gold.  <locus from="2v" to="15r"/>
							</decoNote>
							<decoNote type="illustration">2 textual illustrations.<locus n="44v, 45v"/>
							</decoNote>
							<decoNote type="marginal">26 marginal illustrations.<locus n="16v, 22v, 23r, 26v, 27r, 28r, 32v, 42r, 42v, 43r, 43v, 46r, 47r, 50r, 55r, 56v, 61r, 62r, 66r, 66v, 67r, 67v, 68r, 78v, 83r, 85r"/>
							</decoNote>
							<decoNote type="border">Embellished vertical band between the two text columns.<locus n="22v, 23r, 55r, 56r, 61r, 66v, 67r, 67v, 68r, 68v, 70v, 73r, 78v, 78v, 85r"/>
							</decoNote>
							<decoNote type="initial">36 initial-word panels in gold, many with foliate decoration in colours. <locus n="16v, 22v, 24v, 26v, 27r, 30v, 31v, 32v, 33v, 41v, 44v, 47r, 50r, 51r, 53r, 55v, 56v, 57v, 59v, 61r, 65v, 66r, 66v, 67r, 67v, 68r, 68v, 70v, 73r, 73v, 78v, 82r, 83r, 85r, 86r, 87r"/>
							</decoNote>
							<decoNote type="initial">
								<locus n="31v, 34v, 36v, 38r, 40v"/>5 initial-words with zoomorphic letters.</decoNote>
							<decoNote type="initial">Numerous initial words in gold and, silver and in colours.</decoNote>
							<decoNote type="border">One decorated title page. (Added in the 17th century. All the seventeenth-century decorations were painted on blank pages of the fourteenth-century codex.)<locus n="2r"/>
							</decoNote>
							<decoNote type="other">One heraldic deivce. (Added in the 17th century. All the seventeenth-century decorations were painted on blank pages of the fourteenth-century codex.)<locus n="16r"/>
							</decoNote>
							<decoNote type="border">13 full borders decorated with leaves on the reverse side of the full-page miniatures framing a mnemonic poem on the laws of Passover. (Added in the 17th century. All the seventeenth-century decorations were painted on blank pages of the fourteenth-century codex.)<locus from="3v" to="15v"/>
							</decoNote>
							<decoNote type="border">One full border decorated with leaves. (Added in the 17th century. All the seventeenth-century decorations were painted on blank pages of the fourteenth-century codex.)<locus n="24r"/>
							</decoNote>
							<note>
								<p>The illuminations of the text consist mainly in the gold, silver, and occasionally coloured letters of first and striking words, placed within coloured designs.</p>
								<p>Bears many censors&apos; erasures. </p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="1r" to="16r"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Illustriations</title>
							<note>
								<p>The illustrations consist of coloured miniatures on gold ground, each page being divided into four equal compartments, with a separate picture in each. </p>
								<p>The history illustrated is that of Genesis and the earlier portion of Exodus.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
